    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-10-25T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-10-25T17:00:00-05:00" n="379"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d379">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BC Indonesia/10–2549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Netherlands</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-10-25T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 25, 1949—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>936. <gloss target="#t_Ushic1">Ushic</gloss> 36. Brit Counselor called his
                    request to advise Director Office Phil and <gloss target="#t_SEA1">SEA</gloss>
                        Affairs<note n="1" xml:id="d379fn1">Charles S. Reed, II.</note> that <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>, feeling considerable concern at
                    deterioration mil conditions <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss>, had
                    considered suggesting to <gloss target="#t_UNCI1">UNCI</gloss> desirability
                    latter making report to <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>; Counselor said <gloss
                        target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> wished <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                        >Dept</gloss>’s views. Brit Counselor advised that <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                        >Dept</gloss> considered conditions <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss>
                    had improved perceptibly last few days; that notable progress made at Hague,
                    that reference such matters to <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> likely to
                    provoke recriminations and disruptive discussions and that for these reasons
                        <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> did not believe suggested report by
                        <gloss target="#t_UNCI1">UNCI</gloss> necessary or desirable unless
                    conditions <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> worsen. Brit Counselor,
                    expressing his personal concurrence <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>’s
                    views, said he wld advise Brit <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> position.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
